-- Citic Telecom Said to Buy 79 Percent of Macau Telecom Operator
-- B y   V i n i c y   C h a n   a n d   J o n a t h a n   B r o w n i n g
-- 2013-01-13T08:54:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-13/citic-telecom-said-to-buy-79-percent-of-macau-telecom-operator.html
Citic Telecom International Holdings
Ltd. (1883)  plans to buy 79 percent of a Macau phone operator for about
$1.16 billion, according to two people with knowledge of the
transaction.  Citic Telecom will buy 51 percent of  Companhia de
Telecomunicacoes de Macau, S.A.R.L.  from  Cable & Wireless
Communications Plc. (CWC)  for about $750 million, the people said,
declining to be identified before the announcement. Citic
Telecom will buy a 28 percent stake from  Portugal Telecom SGPS (PTC) 
SA for about $410 million, the people said.  The three companies signed the agreement yesterday in
London, the people said.  Citic Telecom bought 20 percent of the Macau phone
operator, also known as CTM, in February 2011 for HK$1.4 billion
($180 million).  To contact the reporters on this story:
